<div class="large-8 cell">
<h1>Controls</h1>





<h3>Using Parental Control Tools</h3>
<p>The TV Parental Guidelines work in conjunction with the V-Chip and other parental control tools to allow parents to block programming they don’t want their children to see. V-Chips in television sets and parental control tools offered by cable and satellite providers each work a little bit differently. Instructions for programming your television’s V-Chip can be found in the on-screen menu option or in the television owner’s manual. Additionally, the links below provide both general and step-by-step instructions for programming and utilizing parental control tools.</p>


<p><strong>Satellite Parental Control Instructions</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.mydish.com/support/products/hopper/how-to/set-preferences/controls" target="_blank">Dish Network/EchoStar</a></li>
<li><a href="https://support.directv.com/missing-faq" target="_blank">DirecTV</a></li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Cable Parental Controls</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.controlwithcable.org/" target="_blank">Control Your TV</a></li>
</ul>



<br><br><br><br><br>










